<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="907" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d907">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13196.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In company with the Brazilian Minister, Mr. Long and Mr. Belt, at two
                            o’clock this afternoon I complied with the Department’s instruction to
                            say to General Carranza that the President is arranging to withdraw the
                            American troops from Vera Cruz. The message gave the greatest
                            satisfaction. Suitable reply is being prepared.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>